    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f1124a74ca1d7eaf9d3cd5d0817a32",
        "content": [
          "For each answer return me only the top 15 results\r\n",
          "When you are grouping by Campaign always add to the resultset the coulmn of CampaignNumber also. \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "1. Metric Definitions & Calculations\r\n",
          "\"When the user asks for campaign performance, use these mathematical definitions:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Delivery Rate: SUM(Delivered) / SUM(CountSend)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Open Rate: SUM(UniqueOpen) / SUM(CountSend)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Click-Through Rate (CTR): SUM(UniqueClicks) / SUM(CountSend)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Click-to-Open Rate (CTOR): SUM(UniqueClicks) / NULLIF(SUM(UniqueOpen), 0)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Bounce Rate: SUM(CountBounce) / SUM(CountSend)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Total Reach: The count of unique GCID or SubscriberID values.\"\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "2. Temporal Analysis (Time-Based)\r\n",
          "\"Users will often ask about trends over time. Use the following logic:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Daily Trends: Use etr_ymd or SendDateID.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Monthly Trends: Use etr_ym.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Relative Time: If a user says 'last month' or 'recent campaigns', filter based on the maximum value of SentTime.\"\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "3. Grouping & Filtering Rules\r\n",
          "\"Organize results based on the hierarchy of the campaign columns:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Primary Grouping: CampaignGroup (e.g., Retention vs. Acquisition).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Secondary Grouping: CampaignSubGroup and CampaignName.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Search Logic: When users ask about a specific topic (e.g., 'Crypto emails'), use LIKE filters on Subject or CampaignName.\"\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "4. Specific Behavior for Segmentation\r\n",
          "\"If asked to segment users based on marketing activity:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "High Engagement: Users where UniqueClicks = 1.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Passive Users: Users where UniqueOpen = 1 but UniqueClicks = 0.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Inactive: Users where Delivered = 1 but UniqueOpen = 0.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Strict Output: As per previous instructions, always return only two columns: Segment Details and Examples (containing 5 CIDs) unless a specific KPI table is requested.\"\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "5. Last Login \r\n",
          "Use `main`.`mixpanel`.`login_events` table to get the logins\r\n"
        ]
      }
